modules.description: This module defines a variant type for representing Redis replies in the Redis Serialization Protocol (RESP), including operations to construct and deconstruct values like integers, strings, arrays, and status messages. It supports direct conversions between OCaml types (int, string, array) and RESP values, along with type checks and safe extraction functions. Concrete use cases include parsing Redis server responses and building custom Redis command pipelines that handle various reply types, such as bulk strings, integer replies, and multi-element arrays.
